      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum linear elastic model with nonlinear contact is appropriate for stiffness and yield force prediction under quasi-static loading; material nonlinearity included for post-yield regime.",
      "rationale": "The model employs continuum linear elasticity with bilinear isotropic hardening for the titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) and frictional contact (mu=0.3) at screw-rod and screw-block interfaces. This model form is well-established for quasi-static F1717 loading. Literature (Nagaraja et al., J. Biomech. Eng.) supports this approach. Model form level 3 achieved."
    },
