      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of same material lot; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of test specimens; friction coefficient from published tribological data for Ti-Ti interfaces.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and tangent modulus (1.2 GPa) derived from tensile coupon testing of the same material lot used for bench specimens. Screw geometry from CMM measurements (±0.005 mm). Friction coefficient (0.3) from published Ti-Ti dry contact data. Model input uncertainty quantified via ±1 SD sensitivity analysis. Level 3 achieved."
