      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs from production lot; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to design drawing; traceability to manufacturing lot documented.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled from a single production lot. CMM dimensional inspection of all screws confirmed conformance to design drawing tolerances. Material certificates and lot traceability records are on file. Sample size supports statistical comparison per ASTM E2935. Test samples level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing performed at minimum two load levels or two boundary condition configurations to assess model behavior across operating range.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single ASTM F1717 standard test configuration (compression-bending, 5 mm/min crosshead speed, room temperature). Only one test condition was evaluated. This is a known limitation acknowledged by the assessment team; the achieved level (2) falls below the required level (3) for this factor. The overall credibility assessment proceeds with this gap documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
