      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs (geometry, material, boundary conditions, loading rate) are demonstrably equivalent to experimental test conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry as measured by CMM. Applied displacement rate (5 mm/min quasi-static) is consistent with inertia-free static analysis assumption (inertia effects <0.1% by dynamic scaling). Material properties matched to same lot. Equivalency of input parameters level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
