    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment is Accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged; however, the three primary QoIs all satisfy the pre-specified acceptance bounds (<10% error, E/uval <1.96) and the model form and inputs are well-characterized. The assessment team and regulatory reviewers concur that the FEA framework provides adequate credibility for the intended regulatory use. Supporting methodology is described in the literature cited within this package.",
